{
  "texts": [
    "The bi-polar measure minimizes biased evaluations via \"response substitution\" 56.",
    "That is, while uni-polar measures (e.g., \"How much did this change your opinion?\")",
    "might simply capture participants' a priori evaluation or unrelated individual differences, the current measure focuses on participants' evaluations of the ads' relative effectiveness.",
    "Effectiveness was calculated as the average score across the two bi-polar items assessed for each ad (see Fig.",
    "S1 for distribution of outcome variables)."
  ]
}